>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qwr1665702624245.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qwr1665702624245.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qwr1665702624245.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qwr1665702624245\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Construct a Component\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Most components can be created following the same basic procedure.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__context_w2938ab1b5b1_w2939ab1b5_w2940ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__topic_d11891e1_d11892e1_d11893e1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5453e1_d5454e1_d5455e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n                  application definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5456e1_d5457e1_d5458e1\">If the component will access data stored in a\n                  database, ensure that you have defined the modeled entities and relationships. For\n                  more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ppe1703162040468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppe1703162040468.html\" title=\"Modeled entities define the data definitions and default behavior for Uniface components accessing the data.\">Define a Modeled Entity</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5459e1_d5460e1_d5461e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11894e1_d11895e1_d11896e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nlq1704964362863.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nlq1704964362863.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create a new component.\">Create a New Component</a>. Uniface has different types of components suited\n               to different purposes.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11897e1_d11898e1_d11899e1\">Desktop applications use forms for the user\n                  interface. Web applications and mobile apps use server pages. All applications can\n                  use services to handle the business logic, but it you're application is\n                  multi-tier, you will also need session services for data access.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5462e1_d5463e1_d5464e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11900e1_d11901e1_d11902e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>. For each component, define its data structure.\n               This controls the data (component entities and fields) used in the component, the\n               order in which data is processed, and the default behavior when it is stored or\n               deleted. In most cases, component entities are created by inserting modeled entities.\n               You can also create non-database entities that are specific to the component.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5465e1_d5466e1_d5467e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11903e1_d11904e1_d11905e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"btl1705400316529.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btl1705400316529.html\" title=\"Use the Write Script worksheet to script the component's functionality, include the actions it executes, the way it responds to events, the validation it performs when data is loaded or stored, and so on.\">Script the Component Behavior</a>. For component\n               entities and fields, write script modules that control component-specific behavior.\n               For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtm1665702624482.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" title=\"A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.\">Script Modules</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5468e1_d5469e1_d5470e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11906e1_d11907e1_d11908e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oxo1705401146228.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxo1705401146228.html\" title=\"Create the layout of dynamic and static server pages using the Design Layout worksheet.\">Create the Component Layout of Server Pages</a>. For presentation components, design the layout and\n               appearance of the component. For server pages, this is done using HTML.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5471e1_d5472e1_d5473e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> to compile the component. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__li_d5474e1_d5475e1_d5476e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11909e1_d11910e1_d11911e1\">Test the component. From the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Actions</span> menu, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Test</span>. This\n               spawns a separate process and activates the exec operation of the component. When the\n               component exits, control returns to the Uniface IDE.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__note_w2944ab1b5b3c11b3b1_w2945ab1b5b3c11b3_w2946ab1b5b3c11_w2947ab1b5b3_w2948ab1b5_w2949ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> You can optionally specify test\n      logicals in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> file to customize the test environment, providing\n      command line switches that override the default behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nyk1665702685792.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nyk1665702685792.html\" title=\"Test logicals enable you to customize the command used to spawn a component for testing using the Actions &gt;Test option in the Component Editor.\">IDE Test Logicals</a>. </div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__result_w2941ab1b5b5_w2942ab1b5_w2943ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__topic_d11912e1_d11913e1_d11914e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwr1665702624245__p_d11915e1_d11916e1_d11917e1\">Create libraries of global objects that components\n               may require access to, such as messages, variables, and global ProcScript functions.\n               For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ryk1705565545612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryk1705565545612.html\" title=\"Create global objects such as global ProcScripts and messages in a runtime library.\">Create and Maintain Global Objects</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a><p>Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Construct a Component Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Construct a Component Most components can be created following the same basic procedure. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . If the component will access data stored in a database, ensure that you have defined the modeled entities and relationships. For more information, see Define a Modeled Entity . Create a New Component . Uniface has different types of components suited to different purposes. Desktop applications use forms for the user interface. Web applications and mobile apps use server pages. All applications can use services to handle the business logic, but it you're application is multi-tier, you will also need session services for data access. Define the Component Structure . For each component, define its data structure. This controls the data (component entities and fields) used in the component, the order in which data is processed, and the default behavior when it is stored or deleted. In most cases, component entities are created by inserting modeled entities. You can also create non-database entities that are specific to the component. Script the Component Behavior . For component entities and fields, write script modules that control component-specific behavior. For more information, see Script Modules . Create the Component Layout of Server Pages . For presentation components, design the layout and appearance of the component. For server pages, this is done using HTML. Click Compile to compile the component. Test the component. From the Actions menu, choose Test . This spawns a separate process and activates the exec operation of the component. When the component exits, control returns to the Uniface IDE. Tip: You can optionally specify test logicals in the ide.asn file to customize the test environment, providing command line switches that override the default behavior. For more information, see IDE Test Logicals . Create libraries of global objects that components may require access to, such as messages, variables, and global ProcScript functions. For more information, see Create and Maintain Global Objects . Related Links Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}